# Task 15 – Adding Reports to Existing Dashboard

## Project

**Virtual Agent–Driven SLA Breach Awareness & Justification System**

---

## Objective

This task integrates all previously created SLA reports into the **SLA Governance Dashboard**, providing IT Managers with a centralized view of SLA performance and compliance.

---

## Navigation

**Platform Analytics → Dashboards**

or

**Reports → Add to Dashboard**

---

## Reports Added

- SLA Breaches by Reason
- SLA Breaches by Assignment Group
- Pending Justifications
- SLA Performance Trend
- Acknowledged vs Unacknowledged Breaches
- Top Assignees with SLA Violations

---

## Dashboard Widgets

| Widget | Report |
|---------|--------|
| Pie | SLA Breaches by Reason |
| Bar | SLA Breaches by Assignment Group |
| List | Pending Justifications |
| Trend | SLA Performance Trend |
| Pie | Acknowledged vs Unacknowledged Breaches |
| Bar | Top Assignees with SLA Violations |

---

## Deliverables

- SLA Governance Dashboard
- Dashboard Layout
- Dashboard URL
- Updated Flow Designer Email
- Configuration Screenshots

---

## Expected Outcome

The dashboard displays all SLA-related reports in a single interface, and its URL is included in the manager notification email to enable quick access to SLA analytics.

---

## Status

**Completed**

